snippet.textDisplay: The two most significant things you can do to make professional quality pizza are use fresh cake yeast (YES, it definitely makes a difference) and ferment your dough in your refrigerator for at least 3 - 4 days to build up all of those great flavors and the chewy texture. Fresh yeast can be difficult to find, but you should be able to buy it from a local bakery if all else fails.  Restaurant Depot has it if you are fortunate enough to have a membership.  You can get a membership if you are part of a non-profit (ex a church cooking group).  I will post my recipe for restaurant quality pizza dough that makes one 16” pizza if I get at least three likes.
